        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1795",
        "content": "Selina, who had been keeping her eye upon him, thought he was going down to the pond to catch frogs, a joy they had planned to share together, and made after him; but Harold, though he heard her footsteps, continued sternly on his high mission, without even looking back; and Selina was left to wander disconsolately among flower beds that had lost-for her-all scent and colour.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
